option.helptext:
When enabled, 7 powerful relics, The Chaos Emeralds, will be hidden throughout Qud during world generation ({{r|requires a new save}}), the locations of which can be traded for in all the places you can learn about rare and powerful relics.

These items were added as an homage to the Sonic The Hedgehog franchise and aren't really designed to be particularly balanced.

For their sheer power they might feel really strong, but for the effort of sourcing them all in a single run they might feel underwhelming.

They are GameUnique and cannot be replicated once they're generated. {{K|Disabling this option will allow for wishing for them directly by their blueprint.}}

{{K|Alternatively, you can wish for "go chaos emerald [color]" to be taken to the location of a given chaos emerald, or wish for "take chaos emerald [color]" to directly be given that chaos emerald. The wish "take chaos emeralds" will plant all 7 directly in your inventory.}}

{{K|Replace "[color]" entirely with one of green, red, blue, yellow, cyan, pink, or orange: "go chaos emerald red".}}

The default is {{w|Enabled}}.
